"adj. 腐臭的 【英】 adj.腐臭的(rotten) 【例】 The vultures descended toward the putrid flesh. adj. 已腐烂的; 道德败坏的; 卑鄙可耻的 【记】put, rid = red: 把你羞辱成脸红的状态－因为你是卑鄙可耻的 【记】音：扑臭的，扑臭而来的腐臭味 putrid (adj.)  early 15c., from Latin putridus, from putrere ""to rot,"" from putris ""rotten, crumbling,"" related to putere ""to stink,"" from PIE root *pu- ""to rot, stink"" (see pus). First in reference to putrid fever, an old name for typhus (also known in Middle English as putrida). Related: Putrification."
